Northwest Europe oil , gas rigs rise in week . The number of active oil and gas rigs in operation offshore northwest Europe rose by eight to 60 in the week to October 9 , consultants Arthur Andersen said . The Norwegian sector rose by three to 15 rigs active , while the U . K . sector was up four at 31 and the Dutch sector was up one at eight rigs . Denmark was unchanged at four rigs while Irish activity was unchanged at one . Onshore drilling activity was down one rig at five , four in the U . K . and one in the Faroe Islands . - - London newsroom + 44 171 542 6280 
